<TEXT>
this year has brought a heady string of successses 
to javier perez de cuellar the un secretarygeneral tempered by 
reminders that enmities built over centuries do not fade easily 
another sobering element is the nearinsolvency of his 
organization which was created in 1945 as the hope of the world 
but in recent years has been called inept or useless at best and 
at worst seriously biased 
the run of success began in april with an agreement for the 
soviet union to withdraw its 100000 soldiers from afghanistan 
after more than eight years of helping the communist government 
fight moslem guerrillas that agreement took six years of un 
mediation 
then in the past two weeks came the iraniraq ceasefire 
direct talks between the belligerents a revival of negotiations on 
a settlement in divided cyprus and acceptance of a un peace plan 
for the disputed western sahara 
un roles also are foreseen in southern africa and cambodia 
where progress has been made toward peaceful settlements 
a sign of growing un popularity is the increased sales of 
tshirts emblazoned with doves of peace and its blueandwhite 
globe emblem 
reality is always present however to keep euphoria from 
getting out of hand 
in geneva the iraniraq peace negotiations that began aug 25 
were deadlocked this week 
no one had expected the enemies to shake hands and make up 
immediately after eight years of war but perez de cuellar admitted 
to frustration nonetheless 
he left the negotiations thursday to meet other commitments 
appointing swedens un ambassador jan eliasson to continue his 
work as mediator 
a new problem arose when the afghan government asked for more 
talks on the unmediated afghan agreement the soviet union said 
this week it had sent jet fighters back into the country to help 
the army fight the rebels who are supported by the united states 
and pakistan 
if all goes well and a larger un role is required to monitor 
regional political settlements the money problem will grow because 
some members including the united states are behind in their dues 
arrears in dues total 600 million the united states owes more 
than 467 million to the regular budget and 70 million to 
peacekeeping operations 
funding is a huge problem un spokesman francois giuliani 
told reporters in geneva this week he said the organization was 
going broke and being forced to use money intended for october 
salaries to pay for the un peacekeepers in iran and iraq where 
the ceasefire began aug 20 
diplomats say they expect the united states and other members 
as in past budget crises to produce the money needed for the 
organization and its peacekeeping operations 
one reason for the new effectiveness of the 159member world 
organization is increased cooperation among the five permanent 
security council members the united states soviet union 
britain china and france according to the diplomats 
they say an afghan agreement was possible because of improved 
eastwest relations and the decision by soviet leader mikhail s 
gorbachev to cut soviet losses and withdraw 
the main un role is that of catalyst ready to enter the 
picture when nations realize their best interests lie in settling 
regional conflicts 
we must be patient perez de cuellar said thursday when 
questioned about lack of progress in the iraniraq talks 
these problems are very difficult and complicated they cannot 
be solved overnight remember how long the afghanistan talks went 
on 
he admitted to frustration at the slow pace however and said 
he had been very busy with meetings on the cyprus and the western 
sahara problems 
recent achievements by the united nations make an impressive 
list and perez de cuellar has been mentioned as a possible 
candidate for the nobel peace prize the 68yearold peruvian 
diplomat says the prize if awarded should go to the organization 
rather than the man 
</TEXT>
