<TEXT>
the associated press has appointed news editors 
in argentina and puerto rico and a correspondent in belgium in a 
trio of foreign moves ap president louis d boccardi announced 
tuesday 
edmund w mccullough news editor in san juan has been named 
news editor in buenos aires mccullough 38 replaces randall l 
hackley who transferred to the foreign desk in new york 
robert t glass assumes the news editor position in san juan 
glass 41 had been a newsman in london since 1981 when he 
transferred from new york 
sally a jacobsen a mexico city newswoman has been appointed 
nato and common market correspondent in brussels jacobsen 42 
replaces robert w burns who transferred to washington dc 
mccullough a native of stamford conn joined the ap in 1981 
working as a newsman in albany and buffalo ny he transferred to 
washington in 1983 as new york regional reporter two years later 
he moved to the world services desk in new york he was assigned to 
san juan in 1986 
glass a native of nashville tenn joined the ap as a newsman 
in 1974 in philadelphia he transferred to the general desk in 1977 
and worked in new york until his assignment to london 
jacobsen a native of gunnison colo joined the ap in 1976 as 
a newswoman in baltimore she transferred to washington three years 
later in 1985 she moved to the foreign desk and was assigned 
later that year to mexico city 
