<TEXT>
china on wednesday successfully launched its 
first experimental weather satellite the wind and cloud no 1 the 
official xinhua news agency said 
the satellite was launched by a long march 4 rocket from a space 
station in taiyuan northcentral china xinhua said 
it will transmit information on clouds the earths surface 
marine water color vegetation growth ocean surface temperatures 
and ice and snow to satellite ground stations worldwide the news 
agency said 
the state council or cabinet and the central military 
commission issued a statement saying the launching is of great 
importance to promoting chinas national economic growth and serves 
as an encouragement to people of all nationalities 
china has launched 23 of its own satellites since starting its 
space program in 1970 and has recovered 11 orbiters since 1975 
most of the previous satellites have been involved in mapping 
it has begun carrying experimental devices owned by foreign 
companies and is trying to establish a satellite launching service 
for foreign customers 
