medical debris that washed ashore this summer threaten the 
livelihood of thousands who work at our beaches and the enjoyment 
of the millions of new yorkers who use the beaches for recreation 
several popular beaches were temporarily closed during the 
states hottest summer in decades when the debris came ashore 
under the bill approved by cuomo penalties of up to four years 
in prison and fines of up to 50000 could be brought against 
people convicted of illegally disposing of socalled red bag 
medical wastes the name refers to waste that is to be thrown out 
in specially marked containers 
previously state law had provided for illegal medical waste 
dumpers to face up to 15 days in jail and fines of up to to 2500 
according to state department of environmental conservation 
spokesman rw groneman 
