provides 2 million to pay for stepped up enforcement of the 
infectious waste disposal rules by the state departments of 
environmental conservation and parks recreation and historic 
preservation 
the bills are aimed at putting teeth into regulations recently 
established by the state environmental conservation and health 
departments that set out guidelines for disposal of medical wastes 
