we have indicated to them it would be bad for them in congress 
and in us public opinion said the official speaking on 
condition of anonymity 
the seven rebel groups based in pakistan are waging a fight for 
control of afghanistan now that the soviet union has begun a 
pullout to end its 8year occupation the rebels are fighting the 
sovietbacked kabul government and are also expected to vie for 
supremacy among themselves 
a report issued by the state department this week said the 
estimated 3 million to 5 million afghan refugees expected to return 
next year from pakistan and iran will need a quick and profitable 
cash crop to make a living on their ravaged lands the cultivation 
of opium and heroin will be extremely tempting the report said 
it urged international agencies coordinating the repatriation of 
afghan refugees to raise the level of public awareness of the 
narcotics problem 
its something were very aware of and weve talked to the 
mujahedeen about said the us official who is involved in the 
repatriation effort 
the state department report said the soviet pullout as well as 
pakistani president zia ulhaqs death last month in a plane crash 
cast serious doubt on the prospects for successful narcotics 
control in southwest asia 
the international narcotics control strategy report is 
issued by the state department every six months to update 
government officials and congress about attempts of some 50 
countries to eradicate drug production and smuggling 
afghanistan already the largest producer of illicit opium in 
southwest asia is likely to be faced with even greater levels of 
opium cultivation in the unsettled conditions following the soviet 
troop withdrawal the report said 
whatever new government is established in kabul after the 
soviets leave will be faced with so many other pressing needs 
that narcotics control may not be given a high priority it said 
in pakistan president zia was a strong supporter of drug 
eradication and his unexpected death introduced serious 
uncertainties in pakistan that may have an impact on narcotics 
control the report said 
the united states has made it clear to the caretaker government 
in pakistan that narcotics control remains a highpriority issue 
in uspakistan relations the document said 
