sailing became the no 1 spectator sport in san 
diego on wednesday as the americas cup got under way and 
enthusiasts tried to grab the best viewing spots on land and sea 
sailors aboard aircraft carriers and waterfront restaurant 
patrons peered through binoculars as the american catamaran stars 
stripes and the massive yacht new zealand moved through san diego 
bay toward the race starting line 
the heavily favored us boat skippered by dennis conner took 
an early lead in the first race of the bestofthree series stars 
amp stripes went on to defeat new zealand by a margin of 18 minutes 
15 seconds covering the 40mile course in 4 hours 5354 seconds 
the next two races are scheduled for friday and if needed 
sunday 
conner was the skipper of the yacht that won the americas cup 
back from australia last year after losing it to the aussies in 
1983 
a crowd gathered on a grassy embankment at embarcadero marina 
park site of the americas cup tourist village to watch the race 
proceedings live on a stadiumsized video screen positioned on a 
barge just offshore 
its going to be fun once we get our kiwi beer said chris 
hammonds 26 of cambridge new zealand who is on the first leg of 
