sikh militants armed with rifles opened 
fire inside a commuter train in northern punjab state wednesday 
killing 10 hindus and wounding 15 before escaping when the train 
stopped police said 
the attack took place as the train approached rure assal station 
near taran tarn 25 miles south of amritsar the sikh holy city 
said sanjiv gupta senior superintendent of police in taran tarn 
police posted near the station saw a group of sikhs running from 
the train into wheat fields but were unable to catch them gupta 
said in an interview 
after searching the train police found 10 hindu passengers dead 
and 15 injured including eight seriously he said 
gupta said ak47 assault rifles were used in the attack 
the train departed amritsar at 615 pm for khemkaren a town 
on the indiapakistan border 45 miles south of amritsar gupta 
said the victims were employed in amritsar and commuted by train 
to their jobs each day 
more than 1870 people have died in violence blamed on sikh 
militants this year police said 
sikh militants have waged a guerrilla campaign for secession 
from india since 1982 at least 4500 people have been killed 
during that time 
sikhs make up less than 2 percent of indias 800 million people 
but form a majority in punjab state militants claim sikhs are 
discriminated against by the majority hindus and want to form an 
independent sikh state within punjab 
