the criticism came during the opening session of a fourday 
conference of foreign ministers from nations that profess 
nonalignment and it was echoed by several other speakers who 
called on the movement to review its role 
delegations from 92 of the movements 101 members attended the 
meeting including 70 foreign ministers the conference is expected 
to map out the movements policies for the rest of the century 
the movement has become a marginal force on the world stage 
producing many declarations after each meeting which appear to 
have no impact singapores representative ambassador kishore 
mahbubani said in a speech 
we will have to reexamine carefully the procedures and 
practices of the movement that have allowed it to stagnate he 
said the central question is this can we attempt some bold 
restructuring within the movement to make it once again a vital 
force on the world stage 
