212 per share compared with 247 million or 190 per share in 
the previous year 
annual sales rose to 487 billion from 449 billion in the 
previous year 
spokesman david hackney said campbells sales and earnings were 
boosted by acquisitions that totaled 600 million including the 
acquisition of britains freshbake foods 
we had strong volume in a number of areas including soup 
frozen food v8 vegetable juice francoamerican pasta campbells 
beans pepperidge farms and vlasic foods said hackney 
campbell president r gordon mcgovern said restructuring 
acquisitions and a renewed concentration on the companys core 
businesses contributed to profit growth 
last year campbell closed four plants in chicago doylestown 
pa pottstown pa and memphis mich the company also sold three 
ingredient plants and its pietros restaurant chain 
